3jjjjo
Jakarta, Indonesia
2140
Reviewed June 11, 2019
Amazing food hidden in an alley
This place was a bit difficult to find but it is defintely a hidden gem. They only offered 4 menu and we tried 3 of them. They're famous for their pancake but the real star was their pork satay. The meat was marinated well and was really juicy and tender, such a delish. Place was packed even at 3pm which was truly a sign of a good restaurants. Be aware of flies though but if you want an authentic local cuisine, this is definitely worth a visit.
Date of visit: June 2019
