ÁêÜÊ≤ô ÂÆ§
Tokyo, Japan
2327
Reviewed April 13, 2019
Not for the faint-hearted :)
Awesome food! Walk in, tell them number of people in your party, sit down, and food will be delivered to you. As far as I know, there's no real menu. They will bring out plates of Banh Xeo (Vietnamese pancake), grilled ground meat, fresh veggies, rice papers, and dipping sauce will be delivered to you within a minute. If you want drinks, you can walk up and get some from fridge in the back. Food was tasty and I got no stomach-ache from this place so for me, it was great! But my friends weren't too happy with the cleanliness of the place. Yes, servers seem to handle leftover rice papers with the same hand that handled the cash and rice papers were surely recycled. And house cat was walking all over the kitchen and the restaurant. But I really thought the food was great and only for $3.5, that's a bargain.
