bumblebullstravels
Singapore, Singapore
3220
Reviewed January 19, 2019
probably danang's no.1 eatery
located deep inside a small alley and you have to walk further in to discover this eatery.
the shop was bustling with locals and tourists when we arrived around evening time.
- there is no menu for you. once you are seated, you will be served with their signature dishes.
- How to eat is the big question for tourist like us? you would probably be stumbled like us and watch how others savor their food before digging in.
Steps to eat
1. have a piece of rice paper rested on your palm
2. pick up a crispy pancake and place it on top of the rice paper.
3. add in the vegs
4. twist and turn the lemongrass pork skewer (in the middle of the pancake)
5. wrap the rice paper
6. dip into their special sauce.
7. EAT and repeat the steps above
cost for 2 pax with drinks is approx 135kvnd.
we left satisfied and both agreed this is one of the delight danang has to offer.
Cons
- don't expect hygiene level to be top notched.
- they seem to recycle the pork skewers if there are leftover from previous diners.
